# but disruptive.

TEXT(MODES(
        TeX => "",
        HTML => "<SCRIPT>if (window.jsMath) {jsMath.Click.DblClick = function () {}}</SCRIPT>"
    ));

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT
\(u = $u\), \(v=$v\), and to find
$BR
\[\int\int_R ($u) e^{$prod}dA\]
$BR
where R is the region bounded by \($u = $e,$u=$f,$v=$g\) and \($v=$h\)
$BR
\[\int\int_R ($u) e^{$prod}dA=
\int_\mbox{\{ans_rule(10)\}}^\mbox{\{ans_rule(10)\}}
\int_\mbox{\{ans_rule(10)\}}^\mbox{\{ans_rule(10)\}}
\mbox{\{ans_rule(10)\}}
\hskip{5pt}dudv = \mbox{\{ans_rule(20)\}}\] 
$BR
After the change of variables this integral is simple if done the right way. If you do not see that consult your instructor.
END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;
ANS(Formula("$g")->cmp);
ANS(Formula("$h")->cmp);
ANS(Formula("$e")->cmp);
ANS(Formula("$f")->cmp);
ANS($int->cmp);
ANS(Compute("(e^($h*$f)-e^($h*$e))/$h-(e^($g*$e)-e^($g*$f))/$g")->cmp);

ENDDOCUMENT();